   <font class="MsgSubject">What about low end charmers???</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">03/28/2003 07:19 AM CST</font>
   
   <div align="left">
   <font class="MsgText">As peacedogg said, this nerf is gonna hurt low end players more than any. I am referring to the xp penalty. The aggro is another story(I'll get to that). <p>I have a 34 chanter on 7th hammer, I don't play there anymore. Was my first caster class character. My chanter was meant to be a tradeskill mule till i realized how fun it was. Most of her levels came from grouping. I changed servers, and soloed almost my whole chanter career(literraly), to 50. I still charm solo, post 50, but i group some now. I'm soo glad i got my low end charm soloing out of the way.<p>XP penalty will hurt low end soloers moreso. Charm solo becomes more difficult and less rewarding. reward/risk...not even close to worthwhile(so it sounds). As was said, Charm soloing has been part of the very fabric of enchanters. I don't know much about post 60 charming in the planes, and it sounds like an issue that DOES need to be fixed; BUT, don't water down ALL charms!<p>Charm soloing has been going on as just as long as druid/wizard quadding. Once druids can quad, they can keep going all the way post 50, easily; are they overpowered? I'm not taking a shot at druids, I'm just making a point. The amount of xp gained as a solo druid quadding compared to other players is comparable(pre-60) to the xp chanters get compared to other players soloing post 60. Not only are you solo, but your killing 4 mobs at a time...is the overpowered xp? What about mages soloing? Not to take a shot at mages, but just grab a shot of C3, earth pet, they solo really well without risk of their pet kicking thier butt. Are they gonna make summoned pets take just as much xp as charmed pets? In my opinion it would only be fair if you make charmed pets take xp; if xp penalty is based on how much damage your pet does, than OMFG! Solo charming is over. Chanter solo is pretty much over, except some light blues and very few places your weak animation can take a mob. Are nukes are not bad, but do an ok amount of damage at lower lvls. They just cost ALOT of mana and have long cast/recast time compared to othe nukes. So there goes chanter damage output. Shall we talk about chanter DoTs? Yes, they're a joke.<p>I don't want any of these changes to happen(druid/wizzy xp nerfs and ALL pets taking xp). The point I'm trying to make is that SOE needs to come at this problem with another approach. Just as Peacedogg said, they're mainly hurting the lower characters. The people (in  the monk case) that SOE were targeting w/the nerf are already so uber geared, it don't phase them much(according to my 61 monk buddy, i don't have a monk-so i may be somewhat wrong about that last statement).<p>EQ is a grouping game, but, soloing is sometimes cool and there is nothing wrong with doing it.</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
